# Pereste site imagery
#
# Drop files in here with these EXACT slugs and the components auto-pick them
# up. Until a file lands, a designed placeholder renders in its place — the
# layout never breaks.
#
# ── Hero phone mockups (transparent PNG, ~1800x1014 or similar landscape) ──
#   hero-phone.png         home page hero — left side mockup, e.g. listening screen
#   hearthai-phone.png     /hearthai page hero — different screen (Q&A, conversation)
#
# ── Three-commitments icons (home page approach cards) ──
#   icon-models.svg        "Models built for clinical reality"
#   icon-partnership.svg   "Deployed in partnership"
#   icon-rural.svg         "Rural-first by design"
#
# ── HearthAI approach-card icons (/hearthai page) ──
#   icon-adaptive.svg      "Adaptive — meets each patient at their reading level"
#   icon-grounded.svg      "Grounded — speaks to their actual discharge"
#   icon-onprem.svg        "On-prem — designed for institutional deployment"
#
# Specs:
#   • icons: SVG preferred (scales infinitely, smaller). PNG works too — just
#     export at 80x80 minimum. Components display them at 40x40.
#   • phone mockups: transparent background ideal. PNG or JPG. Under 500KB
#     each (run through tinypng.com if larger).
#
# If you ship them with different filenames, just rename them to the above
# slugs after dropping into this folder.
